      • getContext

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getContext()
        Returns the context as returned by the service. At each step in the chat flow the conversation designer has the ability to add information to the chat context. The context is a map of key value pairs, with the values being any valid JSON objects/primitives.
        Returns:
        a map representing context/state

      • getText

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getText()
        A convenience method for getting the text property from the output object. This is equivalent to calling: 
         List<?> text = null;
 Map<String, Object> output = response.getOutput();
 if (output != null) {
   text = (List<?>) output.get("text");
 }
        Returns:
        an array of strings which is to be displayed/returned to the end user

      • getTextConcatenated

        public java.lang.String getTextConcatenated(java.lang.String separator)
        A convenience method for getting the text property from the output object. The text property is an array of strings. This convenience class concatenates the array, separating each entry with the separator string.
        Parameters:
        separator - the separator
        Returns:
        a concatenation of the strings in the output array, with each string separated by the separator string
